spanishExample: ¿Compras tu desayuno en el lugar que abrió ahí?
englishTranslation: Do you buy your breakfast in the place that opened there?

spanishExample: Compre eso, por favor.
englishTranslation: (formal) Buy that, please.

spanishExample: Sabes que ellos nunca traen nada para sus amiguitos.
englishTranslation: You know they never bring anything for their little friends(dim).

spanishExample: Aun ella cree que yo no traeré nada.
englishTranslation: Even she believes I won’t bring anything.

spanishExample: Va a ir a comprar algo.
englishTranslation: She’s going to buy something.

spanishExample: Traigan esas cosas porque él no trae nada últimamente.
englishTranslation: (plural) Bring those things because he doesn't bring anything lately.

spanishExample: Compró esos tenedores en el lugar que ha abierto cerca de tu casa.
englishTranslation: She bought those forks in the place that has opened near your house.

spanishExample: Sabes que él no va a traerlo.
englishTranslation: You know he’s not going to bring it.

spanishExample: Van a traer muchos regalos, así que abran todos.
englishTranslation: They are going to bring a lot of presents, so open(plural) all of them.

spanishExample: Están completamente de acuerdo y quieren que yo abra la puerta.
englishTranslation: They completely agree and they want me to open the door.

spanishExample: Es absolutamente seguro, así que abra la puerta.
englishTranslation: (formal) It’s absolutely safe, so open the door.

spanishExample: ¡Trae eso! Yo ya lo traje ayer.
englishTranslation: Bring that! I already brought it yesterday.

spanishExample: Por favor, compra la computadora porque yo no la compraré.
englishTranslation: Please, buy the computer because I won’t buy it.

spanishExample: Obviamente estamos vendiendo todos los platos que tú traes.
englishTranslation: Obviously we’re selling all the plates you’re bringing.

spanishExample: Ojalá él traiga su reloj porque tú no lo trajiste.
englishTranslation: Hopefully he brings his watch because you didn’t bring it.

spanishExample: Él abre todos los regalos que yo compro para ellos.
englishTranslation: He opens all the presents I buy for them.

spanishExample: Sabe que no los puede abrir.
englishTranslation: He knows he can’t open them.

spanishExample: Traiga los vasos que compré ayer.
englishTranslation: (formal) Bring the glasses I bought yesterday.

spanishExample: Abre eso ahora, tengo prisa y me tengo que ir enseguida.
englishTranslation: Open that now, I’m in a hurry and I have to leave right away.

spanishExample: Vende todos los objetos que tú le compraste.
englishTranslation: He’s selling all the objects you bought him.

spanishExample: ¿Puedes traerme eso?
englishTranslation: Can you bring me that?

spanishExample: ¡Vende eso! Quiero que cualquier persona lo compre.
englishTranslation: Sell that! I want any person to buy it.

spanishExample: Hay muchísimas personas, pero nadie ha comprado eso.
englishTranslation: There are a whole lot of people, but nobody has bought that.

spanishExample: ¿Por qué has vendido esa cuchara? Te dije que no la podías vender.
englishTranslation: Why have you sold that spoon? I told you you couldn’t sell it.

spanishExample: La casita está definitivamente lejos, así que tráeme eso, por favor.
englishTranslation: The little house is definitely far away, so bring me that please.

spanishExample: ¿Por qué compra eso para el gato? ¿Y nuestra cena?
englishTranslation: Why is he buying that for the cat? And our dinner?

spanishExample: Ellos venden lo mismo que ella vendió.
englishTranslation: They are selling the same that she sold.
